於《{{link-en|小小選美皇后|Toddlers & Tiaras}}》上現身的家長亦為抨擊對象。批評者批評他們誘使自身的子女以外相換取他人的目光和獎勵。《小小選美皇后》於2009年首播，其講述參賽者及其家長如何為周末的選美活動進行準備。此一節目為了避免表露製作者的立場，而刻意不採用旁白。不過才藝比賽部分則引發了不少爭議。引發爭議的原因有讓孩童抽假煙<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/toddlers-tiaras-shocker-4-year-old-destiny-smokes-cigarette-onstage-article-1.1148847|title='Toddlers & Tiaras' girl smokes cigarette on stage|website=Nydailynews.com|access-date=2017-05-01|archive-date=2017-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815080607/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/toddlers-tiaras-shocker-4-year-old-destiny-smokes-cigarette-onstage-article-1.1148847|dead-url=no}}</ref>、強迫女童戴上胸墊<ref>{{cite news|title=Should a Toddlers & Tiaras mom lose custody of her child?|url=https://theweek.com/articles/472959/should-toddlers--tiaras-mom-lose-custody-child|accessdate=2018-01-27|work=The Week|date=2012-08-21|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023535/https://theweek.com/articles/472959/should-toddlers--tiaras-mom-lose-custody-child|dead-url=no}}</ref>、容許女童穿得像妓女般<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/toddlers-tiaras-star-dresses-prostitute-pageant-draws-criticism-parent-tv-council-article-1.954100|title='Toddlers and Tiaras' star dresses as prostitute|website=Nydailynews.com|access-date=2017-05-01|archive-date=2017-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815063839/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv-movies/toddlers-tiaras-star-dresses-prostitute-pageant-draws-criticism-parent-tv-council-article-1.954100|dead-url=no}}</ref>、為了子女有足夠體力表演而餵食高[[卡路里|卡路里]]糖份補充劑<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2083119/Toddlers-Tiaras-mothers-DOPING-daughters-drinks-spiked-pageant-crack.html|title=Are Toddlers and Tiaras mothers DOPING their daughters? Girls' drinks spiked with 'pageant crack and go-go juice' in most shocking scenes yet|website=Dailymail.co.uk|access-date=2017-05-01|archive-date=2017-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102110114/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2083119/Toddlers-Tiaras-mothers-DOPING-daughters-drinks-spiked-pageant-crack.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、為子女的臉部抹蠟<ref>{{cite news|last1=von Pfetten|first1=Verena|title=Mom Forces Scared 5-Year-Old To Get Eyebrows Waxed|url=http://www.styleite.com/media/toddlers-tiaras-eyebrow-wax/|accessdate=2018-01-27|work=Styleite|date=2011-01-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922144353/http://www.styleite.com/media/toddlers-tiaras-eyebrow-wax/|archivedate=2012-09-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===進食障礙===
參賽的孩童常為公眾的注目焦點。他们的職責就是合作與維持美貌，而體重則為當中的關注要點。故此，不少參賽者患上了像[[神经性厌食症|神经性厌食症]]般的進食障礙。他們为了保持「合适」的体重，而故意让自己挨饿。此外一部分比賽會要求女孩們穿上緊身裝，使得她們對於[[體重管理|體重管理]]更為在意<ref>Wonderlich, A., Ackard, D., & Henderson, J. (2005). "Childhood Beauty Pageant Contestants: Associations with Adult Disordered Eating and Mental Health". ''Eating Disorders'', 13(3), 291-301. doi:10.1080/10640260590932896</ref>。

==== 2005年研究 ====
在一項於2005年推出的研究中，研究者找來了22名女性，當中一半自小就參與選美比賽，另外一半則沒參與過任何選美。他們為兩組女性進行了各式各樣的比較，包括身體滿意度、BMI、年齡。結果發現自小參與選美比賽者一般較不滿意自己的身體，且較多出現冲动行为失调和不相信他人的情況。不過兩組在抑鬱、自尊、[[神經性暴食症|神經性暴食症]]、身體意象等方面沒有顯著差異。研究者表示，由於此一研究樣本過少，故難以得出有效概括<ref name=friend>Wonderlich, Anna, Diann Ackard, Judith Henderson. “Childhood Beauty Pageant Contestants: Associations with Adult Disordered Eating and Mental Health.” ''Eating Disorders 13'' (2005) : 291-301</ref>。

===兒童商品化===
部分批評者指責，選美比賽把兒童當作可產生商業利益的產品般宣傳。他們形容這是一筆交易——家长花钱购置服装、化妆、饰品，以换取獲得现金回饋的機會<ref>Wolfe, L. (2012). "Darling Divas or Damaged Daughters? The Dark Side of Child Beauty Pageants and an Administrative Law Solution". ''Tulane Law Review'', 87(2), 427-455.</ref>。

===性化===
{{main|兒童選美比賽與性化}}
參賽者為了贏得比賽，而在很小的時候就需透過各種手段（比如服装、化妆）來裝扮自己，這便導致了[[性化|性化]]的出現<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bartlett|first=Myke|title=Sex Sells: Child Sexualization and the Media|journal=Screen Education|year=2008|accessdate=}}</ref>。某些选美比赛鼓励参赛者打扮得像成年女性般，從化浓妆到挑逗的面部表情，無一不齊<ref>{{cite web|title=Sexualization of Girls|url=http://www.apa.org/pi/women/programs/girls/report.aspx|publisher=American Psychological Association|access-date=2012-07-11|archive-date=2011-09-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110901235730/http://www.apa.org/pi/women/programs/girls/report.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

孩童可能從中了解到，要性化自身，才能獲得較多關注。這樣的話不僅向之鼓勵性，還為之灌輸性可以作為達到目的的一種手段<ref name=Vernon>{{cite web|last=Vernon|first=Wiehe|title=Nothing Pretty in Child Pageants|url=http://www.kentucky.com/2011/08/14/1844981/nothing-pretty-in-child-pageants.html|publisher=kentucky.com|accessdate=2012-04-18|archive-date=2014-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530111705/http://www.kentucky.com/2011/08/14/1844981/nothing-pretty-in-child-pageants.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在马里兰州执业的心理学家席德·布朗（Syd Brown）在接受ABC新聞採訪時表示：「對於不少人而言，『看似成熟一點』為『看似性感一點』的同義詞。我不認為讓少女這麼關注性是一件好事……如果你要一个6岁的孩子表現得像16岁般，你就等同於告訴她再性感誘惑一點」<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/story?id=126315&page=1|title=Beauty Pageants Draw Children and Criticism|date=2006-01-06|publisher=[[ABC新聞|ABC News]]|access-date=2017-05-01|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127015649/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/story?id=126315&page=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===反駁===
哈佛大学的本科研究者希拉里·莱维（Hillary Levy）發現，许多容許子女參賽的家长认为，他们的孩子能從中學習如何表露出風度和自信。對於部分家長而言，選美比賽能讓有先天缺陷的孩子與更多的人交流，使之發現自身跟其他人沒什麼不同<ref>Cromie, William. "The Whys and Woes of Beauty Pageants". ''Harvard University Gazette'' (2000): n. pag. Web. <http://news.harvard.edu {{Wayback|url=http://news.harvard.edu/ |date=20201214075055 }}>.</ref>。

